  "district_type": "Unified K-12",
  "district_web_research": {
    "additional_findings": "Large unified district. Publishes a dedicated 'Autism Specific Programs and Behavior Support' page describing a continuum of Autism Specific Classrooms from preschool through adult transition (ages 3-22). District-employed Behavior Intervention Specialists (BIS) provide site supervision, consultation, training, and programming assistance using evidence-based practices. Named contacts: Sean Viney (Autism Coordinator) and Jenny Bailey (Administrative Assistant). District is part of its own Irvine SELPA, which partners with CAPTAIN for evidence-based autism practices. Specific autism classroom locations (site by site) are not published on this page. BCBA credential is not explicitly stated for the Behavior Intervention Specialists.",
